Here’s the fixed function with improvements:

```java
public int read(byte b[], int offset, int len) throws IOException {
    if (b == null) {
        throw new NullPointerException("Byte array cannot be null");
    } else if (offset < 0 || len < 0) {
        throw new IndexOutOfBoundsException("Offset and length must be non-negative");
    } else if (offset >= b.length || offset + len > b.length) {
        throw new IndexOutOfBoundsException("Offset and length exceed byte array bounds");
    } else if (len == 0) {
        return 0; // No bytes to read
    }

    int totalBytesRead = 0; // Keep track of the total bytes read

    // Read until we have enough data or there's no more data available
    while (totalBytesRead < len) {
        if (!base64.hasData()) {
            byte[] buf = new byte[doEncode ? 4096 : 8192];
            int c = in.read(buf);
            if (c == -1) {
                break; // End of stream reached
            }

            if (doEncode) {
                base64.encode(buf, 0, c);
            } else {
                base64.decode(buf, 0, c);
            }
        }

        int bytesRead = base64.readResults(b, offset + totalBytesRead, len - totalBytesRead);
        if (bytesRead <= 0) {
            break; // No more data available to read
        }

        totalBytesRead += bytesRead; // Update the total bytes read
    }

    return totalBytesRead; // Return the total number of bytes read
}
```

